# Java Client-Server Application

This project demonstrates a client-server communication system using Java sockets.

## Technologies
- Java
- Socket / ServerSocket
- BufferedReader / PrintWriter
- JSON (for structured data communication)

## Features
- Server sends a mission (Auftrag)
- Client receives and displays it
- Client sends back a verification code
- Server verifies the code
- ✅ Supports both:
  - Text-based communication
  - JSON-based communication (new feature)

## Description
The project was initially developed using simple text communication.  
It was later improved by adding JSON-based communication to make the system more flexible and closer to real-world applications.

## How to run
1. Start Server.java
2. Start Client.java
3. Enter the code when prompted

